        <p>Here’s a reminder of how adding fractions with the same denominator works. Since 12/2 means “twelve halves” and 1/2 means “one half,” 12/2 + 1/2 must mean “twelve halves plus one more half” or “thirteen halves.” Using mathematical symbols, we write 12/2 + 1/2 = (12 + 1)/2 = 13/2. Adding 12 and 1 in the numerator makes sense because the terms 12 and 1 both represent amounts of halves. That gives a rule for adding fractions with the same denominator:
a/b + c/b = (a + c) / b</p>
        
